<DocsLayout title="Joining" description="Join a hosted world with an etmc:// link or a join code.">
  <h2>With an <code>etmc://</code> link (recommended)</h2>
  <p>
    The host shares an <code>etmc://v1/…</code> link (from <strong>Session status → Copy etmc:// link</strong>,
    <code>/etmc invite</code>, or a dedicated server's console). Joining needs no etmc menu and opens
    <strong>no local port</strong>:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Minecraft → <strong>Multiplayer</strong> → <strong>Add Server</strong> (or <strong>Direct Connect</strong>).</li>
    <li>Paste the <code>etmc://…</code> link into the <em>Server Address</em> field.</li>
    <li><strong>Join Server</strong>. etmc shows <em>Establishing P2P connection</em> while it sets up a direct link, then connects.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    If a direct peer-to-peer link can't be established quickly (e.g. strict NAT), click
    <strong>Join now anyway</strong> to connect over the relay instead.
  </p>

  <h2>With a join code</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Open the menu (<span class="kbd">G</span>) → <strong>Join with a code</strong>.</li>
    <li>Paste the <code>ETMC1:…</code> code (or use <strong>Paste from clipboard</strong>).</li>
    <li>etmc adds the server to your <strong>Multiplayer</strong> list — open it and click to connect.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>Or via command: <code>/etmc join &lt;code&gt;</code>.</p>

  <h2>What happens</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>etmc starts an EasyTier instance (no-TUN, DHCP) on the host's network;</li>
    <li>an <strong><code>etmc://</code> link</strong> rides the mesh's data plane directly — <em>no loopback socket, no port</em>;</li>
    <li>a <strong>join code</strong> opens a loopback proxy at <code>127.0.0.1:&lt;port&gt;</code> and tunnels it to the host over the mesh.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Either way, from Minecraft's perspective it's a normal server connection, so resource packs, mods and the
    server list all behave as usual. The HUD shows each peer as <em>p2p</em> or <em>relay</em>. See
    <a href="/docs/compatibility">Mod compatibility</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Joining a dedicated server</h2>
  <p>
    A Paper server prints both a join code and an <code>etmc://</code> link on startup (and via <code>/etmc code</code>) —
    paste the link into Add Server / Direct Connect, or use the code. If an admin published a config file instead,
    use <a href="/docs/connect-url">Connect via config URL</a>.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
